stories.title: Pakistan v India
stories.subTitle: Third One-Day International
stories.summary: What a difference a bowler's pitch makes. On a rugged surface, much like the surrounding terrain, a target of 245 looked as menacing as 300-plus in the earlier games.

stories.title: Razzaq - the occasional allrounder
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 3rd ODI, Peshawar
stories.summary: How Pakistan fare in the remainder of the series may well depend on how often Abdul Razzaq meets expectations
stories.byline: The Pakistan Verdict by Osman Samiuddin

stories.title: The hard yards
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 3rd ODI, Peshawar
stories.summary: Pakistan won another closely contested game because Yasir Hameed did what no other batsman on either side could do - convert a start into something substantial
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Dileep Premachandran

stories.title: Hameed and Razzaq overpower India
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 3rd ODI, Peshawar
stories.summary: Abdul Razzaq and Moin Khan took Pakistan to their victory target of 245 with 16 balls to spare
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Amit Varma
